Parliament's Standing Committee on Public Accounts has reported on its findings, following a two-day visit to the Medupi and Kusile power stations. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Parliament's Standing Committee on Public Accounts reported on its findings following a two-day visit to the Medupi and Kusile power stations. The power stations have been running over budget and deadlines. READ: Eskom's Medupi unit one synchronised There's been more than R19-billion in irregular expenditure and a ballooning debt of R380-billion in the 2017/2018 financial year. Scopa member Robert Lees said one of the major concerns is the environmental impact of Medupi which currently is not operating within regulatory frameworks on pollution. READ: Scopa to conduct oversight visits at Eskom plants Lees also raised ongoing problems with the completion of the construction at Kusile power station and the current reliance on coal.